parameters.original_question: Here is the meta data of the expriment: Seven adult patients with newly diagnosed, MGMT-unmethylated, EGFRvIII-positive glioblastoma underwent a phase 1 study combining systemically infused EGFRvIII\u2010targeted CAR T cells with pembrolizumab. After surgical resection and hypofractionated radiation (40 Gy in 15 fractions), each patient received up to three cycles of CAR T cells (2 \u00d7 10^8 cells/dose) co-administered with anti-PD-1, followed by pembrolizumab monotherapy. Safety was monitored by dose-limiting toxicity criteria and clinical adverse\u2010event grading. Tumors were resected at radiographic progression (7\u2013179 days post-infusion), providing paired pre- and post-treatment specimens in three patients and post-treatment tissue in four. Data modalities included single-cell RNA sequencing and TCR sequencing on CD45-enriched cells, flow cytometry phenotyping of infusion products with a 30\u2010marker panel, quantitative PCR for CAR transgene detection, and bulk NGS assessment of EGFRvIII expression. Peripheral blood kinetics were tracked by CAR copies per \u03bcg DNA. Comparative analyses involved prior recurrent GBM CAR T trials. The design allowed dissection of CAR T-cell infiltration, phenotypic shifts in myeloid and T-cell subsets, and interferon-stimulated signatures correlating with outcomes.
